<caption pageId="33" pageNumber="100" startId="33.[227,270,1224,1250]" targetBox="[229,1437,664,1179]" targetPageId="33">
<paragraph blockId="33.[227,1437,1224,1286]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,327,1224,1250]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">Fig. 26.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[341,650,1225,1251]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="saharensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[341,650,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">Maccoyoceras saharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[665,763,1225,1251]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Oued Temertasset (all Korn 
<emphasis box="[1208,1267,1225,1251]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">et al</emphasis>
. 2002 Coll.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,248,1260,1286]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">A</emphasis>
. Holotype MB.C.30480.1. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,589,1260,1286]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">B</emphasis>
. Paratype MB.C.30481. Scale bar units =1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption pageId="33" pageNumber="100" startId="33.[227,270,1931,1957]" targetBox="[227,1436,1401,1885]" targetPageId="33">
<paragraph blockId="33.[225,1436,1931,2029]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,324,1931,1957]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">Fig. 27.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[337,645,1932,1958]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="saharensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[337,645,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">Maccoyoceras saharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[658,754,1932,1958]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from Oued Temertasset (both Korn 
<emphasis box="[1213,1270,1932,1958]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">et al</emphasis>
. 2002 Coll.). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,248,1967,1993]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">A</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30480.1. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[747,767,1967,1993]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">B</emphasis>
. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30480.1, at ww =16.2 mm, wh=14.8 mm. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,426,2002,2028]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">C</emphasis>
. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30481. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[927,948,2002,2028]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">D</emphasis>
. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30481, at
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="33.[228,863,2037,2064]" box="[228,863,2037,2064]" pageId="33" pageNumber="100">
ww= 
<quantity box="[293,401,2037,2064]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.09" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="10.9">10.9 mm</quantity>
, wh= 
<quantity box="[472,579,2037,2064]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.48" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="14.8">14.8 mm</quantity>
. Scale bar units = 
<quantity box="[787,858,2037,2064]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="100" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[523,909,230,256]" lastBlockId="34.[227,1436,303,365]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
KORN D. &amp; BOCKWINKEL J., Early Carboniferous nautiloids from 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1436,229,255]" name="Algeria" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Algeria</collectingCountry>
depression on the venter, a slightly deeper, very broadly rounded lobe on the flank and a very shallow internal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[390,498,339,365]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[227,270,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-11@33.[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 27. Maccoyoceras saharensis sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30480.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30480.1, at ww =16.2 mm, wh=14.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30481. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30481, at" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Fig. 27B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,1436,405,613]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<typeStatus box="[227,330,406,432]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30481 shows the chambered remains of two whorls that touch but do not overlap (
<figureCitation box="[235,346,441,468]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[227,270,1224,1250]" captionTargetBox="[229,1437,664,1179]" captionTargetId="figure-110@33.[227,1437,658,1186]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 26. Maccoyoceras saharensis sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype MB.C.30480.1. B. Paratype MB.C.30481. Scale bar units =1 mm." pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Fig. 26B</figureCitation>
). On the outer whorl with 
<quantity box="[674,760,442,468]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
whorl height, the profile is subquadrate (ww/wh =1.04) with a wider, flattened venter, weakly divergent, also flattened flanks and a more tightly rounded dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[330,438,514,540]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[227,270,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-11@33.[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 27. Maccoyoceras saharensis sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30480.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30480.1, at ww =16.2 mm, wh=14.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30481. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30481, at" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Fig. 27C</figureCitation>
). The penultimate whorl, 
<quantity box="[738,828,514,541]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" unit="mm" value="3.8">3.8 mm</quantity>
high, is rounded-triangular in profile and somewhat depressed (ww/wh =1.28). The suture line is similar to that of the 
<typeStatus box="[1007,1113,550,576]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">holotype</typeStatus>
, but shows a higher ventral area with a slightly deeper external lobe (
<figureCitation box="[713,822,586,613]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[227,270,1931,1957]" captionTargetBox="[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetId="figure-11@33.[227,1436,1401,1885]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 27. Maccoyoceras saharensis sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30480.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30480.1, at ww =16.2 mm, wh=14.8 mm. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30481. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30481, at" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Fig. 27D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,341,653,679]" box="[227,341,653,679]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,653,679]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,653,679]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[227,1438,700,908]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,534,700,726]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="saharensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,534,700,726]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Maccoyoceras saharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[546,641,701,727]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from the other species of the genus by the whorl profile form with a strongly rounded ventrolateral shoulder. Another difference could be the strength of the ornament; in 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[388,553,773,799]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Maccoyoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="saharensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[388,553,773,799]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">M. saharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[563,655,773,799]" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
no spiral lines were impressed into the internal mould. However, since no shell specimens of the new species are known, it is impossible to say whether spiral lines were actually present. It is therefore also possible that the new species belongs to another genus, for example 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyatt" authorityYear="1893" box="[227,356,882,907]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Lispoceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="34" pageNumber="101" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,356,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="101">Lispoceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
